SERVER CREATION
 

 BASIC COMMANDS
 ------------------------------------

 1) Creating package- json - npm init
 2) Install Express - npm i Express
 3) Install JWT - npm i jsonwebtoken
 4) Install mongoose - npm i mongoose
 5) Install CORS - npm i cors


 BASIC STEPS
 --------------------------------------

 1) Create a folder
 2) Create package.json
 3) Install express
 4) Create Index.js
 5) Import Express inside the index.js
 6) Create app using Express
 7) Setup port number
 8) Resolving http methods
 9) HTTP response code
    1xx- Information
    2xx- Success
    3xx- Redirection
    4xx- Client Error
    5xx- Server Error
10) JWT (JSON WEB TOKEN)- For authentication
    jwt.sign()
11) Middleware -
    1)application specific middleware - for entire application
    next()
    2)router specific middleware - token verification -verify()

    for specific component
12) Database Integration- 
     install mongoose
     To connect with mongodb via mongoose
     create model using mongoose
13) Asynchronous function Resolving - promise
     resolve - then()
     reject - catch()
14) CORS - Cross Origin Resource Sharing
    install corse
